14/03/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government declared a day of national mourning Sunday (14 March) in honour of Romanian citizens killed in the Madrid terror attacks and as an expression of solidarity with the Spanish people.
According to the Romanian Embassy in Spain, at least seven Romanians died in the train bombings Thursday.
Another body was awaiting identification.
At least 60 Romanians were wounded in the blasts;
25 remained hospitalised.
The government says security at the embassy in Spain and other diplomatic institutions has been strengthened.
At least two Bulgarians were killed in Madrid, while several others are still missing.
Bulgaria also stepped up security measures following the terror attacks, for which al-Qaida now claims responsibility.
(Mediafax, bTV - 13/03/04;
Rompres - 12/03/04)
